cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.LG

This paper deals with the problem of ON/OFF scheduling of self-powered millimeter wave base stations in the presence of energy harvesting uncertainty. This problem is related to network optimization, energy harvesting, and online algorithms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory) due to the focus on energy harvesting uncertainty, cs.SY (Systems and Control) due to the need for smart scheduling, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) due to the use of the ski rental framework, and cs.LG (Machine Learning) due to the use of competitive analysis.
